  "prompt": "How can guys last long during sex?",
  "response": "Lasting longer during sex is a common concern for many men. Here are some practical tips that can help:\n\n### 1. **Practice Good Communication**\n   - Openly discuss your feelings, needs, and concerns with your partner. This reduces anxiety and helps you stay relaxed.\n\n### 2. **Strengthen Your Pelvic Floor**\n   - Exercises like **Kegels** (tightening and releasing the pelvic floor muscles) can improve control over ejaculation.\n\n### 3. **Experiment with the Start-Stop Technique**\n   - During sex or masturbation, pause stimulation when you feel close to climax, wait until the urge subsides, and then resume. This trains your body to delay ejaculation.\n\n### 4. **Try the Squeeze Technique**\n   - When you feel close to orgasm, gently squeeze the base of the penis for a few seconds to reduce arousal. Release and continue when the urge subsides.\n\n### 5. **Focus on Breathing**\n   - Slow, deep breaths can help you stay calm and delay ejaculation.\n\n### 6. **Experiment with Positions**\n   - Certain positions may reduce stimulation and help you last longer (e.g., positions where you control the depth and pace).\n\n### 7. **Use Thicker Condoms or Desensitizing Products**\n   - Condoms designed for extended performance or desensitizing sprays/gels could reduce sensitivity.\n\n### 8. **Build Endurance Through Practice**\n   - Regular masturbation can help you understand your arousal patterns and practice delaying ejaculation.\n\n### 9. **Manage Stress and Anxiety**\n   - Stress and performance anxiety can contribute to premature ejaculation. Meditation, yoga, or therapy can help.\n\n### 10. **Focus on Foreplay**\n   - Spend more time on foreplay to satisfy your partner and reduce pressure on lasting longer during intercourse.\n\n### 11. **Stay Physically Active**\n   - Regular exercise improves stamina and overall sexual health.\n\n### 12. **Consider Medical Advice**\n   - If premature ejaculation is a persistent issue, consult a healthcare professional. Treatments may include therapy, medication, or other interventions.\n\n### 13. **Take Breaks During Sex**\n   - Pausing to switch positions or focus on your partner can give you time to cool down.\n\n### 14. **Avoid Overthinking**\n   - Focus on the experience rather than worrying about how long you\u2019re lasting. Enjoyment is key.\n\nEvery individual is different, so experiment to find what works best for you. If the issue persists, seeking advice from a healthcare provider or sex therapist can be helpful.",
